Program: Discovery
Title: Genetic causes of deafness
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx0k
Last Broadcast Date: 17 November 1997
How a Costa Rican family are helping scientists understand deafness. A 20-year study - involving a family who have disposition to go profoundly deaf - has found that genetics plays a much bigger role in hearing than had at first been thought. Also in the programme cancer research and a form of cell suicide treatment and the atomic energy industry. Presenter: Graham Easton Show less